According to Freeman (2017) true bulges come from mergers, while instabilities in disks provide bars and pseudo bulges as in the Milky Way. Our thick disk (which does not have arms, nor do other thick disks (they are nearly but not quite ubiquitous)) formed 11–12 Gyrs ago, at z=2–2.5\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
