There are also many galaxy-evolution issues that do not obviously interact with spiral structure, for instance the correlation of stellar masses with central Super Massive Black Hole masses (Heckman and Best 2014) and deciding whether they radiate enough ultraviolet to re-ionize the universe at z≈6\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
