In another approach quantum gravity is described as a network that self-organizes into a discrete 4-D universe, in analogy to the ferro-magnetic Ising model for space-time vertices with an anti-ferromagnetic Ising model for the links. The ground state self-organizes as a new type of low-clustering graph with finite Hausdorff dimension 4 (Trugenberger 2015). Once again, this work does not appear to directly lead to the Λ\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
